That every Minister being a person of good Conversation,Ministers Chosen by the major part of the Inhabitants, to be the Minister of such Town. Able, Learned and Orthodox, that shall be Chosen by the major part of the Inhabitants in any Town, at a Town-Meeting duly warned for that purpose, (notice thereof being given to the Inhabitants fifteen days before the time for such Meeting
                     •
                  ) shall be the Minister of such Town; and the whole Town shall be obliged to pay towards his Settlement and Maintainance, each man his several proportion thereof.

That it shall be in the Liberty of any Maintiff,Plaintiffs liberty to begin his Suit in the Inferiour or Supe
•••• Court. to begin his Suit, either in the Inferiour or Superiour Court, at his pleasure; and where the Original Process is made out of the Superiour Court, the Party Cast shall have Liberty to Review his Case in the said Superiour Court, ones and no more PROVIDED Nevertheless, That none of the said Inferiour Court shall Receive any Action under the value of Forty Shillings;
nor shall any Action under the value of Ten Pounds be brought into the Superiour Court,No Action under Ten Pounds to come originally to the Superiour Court. unless where Freehold is concerned, or upon Appeal.
